.SH NAME
.PP
ibv_get_device_index \- get an RDMA device index
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
#include <infiniband/verbs.h>

int ibv_get_device_index(struct ibv_device *device);
\f[R]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]ibv_get_device_index()\f[R] returns stable IB device index as it is
assigned by the kernel.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
\f[B]ibv_get_device_index()\f[R] returns an index, or \-1 if the kernel
doesn\[cq]t support device indexes.
